7 An Act relating to higher education; creating the
Selecting Neutral Accreditors Act; defining terms;
8 directing the board of regents of each institution of
higher education to review accrediting agencies to
9 determine if such agencies have adopted or used
certain diversity, equity, and inclusion practices or
10 procedures in connection with accreditation within
the past five years; requiring the board of regents
11 to begin the process to change accrediting agency if
practice or procedure is found; permitting board of
12 regents to select an accrediting agency who had
diversity, equity, and inclusion practices or
13 procedures within the past five years if the agency
formally repeals practice or procedure and certifies
14 the agency will not use practice or procedure in the
future; requiring the board of regents to report if
15 no qualifying accrediting agency is found; requiring
the board of regents to review applicable accreditors
16 for compliance prior to beginning any new
accreditation or pre-accreditation process or
17 renewal; authorizing Attorney General to request
information; finding presumption of diversity,
18 equity, and inclusion practices or procedures if
failure to respond by accrediting agency; authorizing
19 Attorney General to provide notice of presumption;
voiding certain agreements between institutions and
20 accrediting agencies; providing for investigation and
enforcement by Attorney General; providing for
21 noncodification; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
